The balance of a prime $p$ in a factorization $f$ is defined as $f.\text{sum}(\lambda q, q \mid p \Rightarrow \text{ord}_{p}(q) \cdot \text{val}_{p}(q))$, where $\text{ord}_{p}(q)$ is the exponent of $p$ in the prime factorization of $q$ and $\text{val}_{p}(q)$ is the $p$-adic valuation of $q$.

